Tokyo rubber futures end firmer on short - covering . Japanese rubber futures ended firmer across the board on Monday , as cautionary views that prices were too low after falls last week stimulated some short - covering , traders said . Prices ranged from flat to 0 . 9 yen per kg higher . Benchmark September was up 0 . 8 yen at 150 . 3 yen . The market started the day on a firmer note , as relatively cheap prices compared with overseas markets attracted sporadic short - covering . But bearish sentiment remained intact . " The upside may be limited as selling could emerge when the benchmark approaches 152 or 153 yen , " one trader said . 
